    <briefdescription>
<para>Hardware Abstraction Layer (HAL) for vital signs acquisition. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This interface decouples the GUI from the data source. In production, replace <ref refid="sim__vitals_8c" kindref="compound">sim_vitals.c</ref> with hw_driver.c that reads from real hardware (e.g., serial port, USB medical device, ADC) without changing any other source file.</para>
<sect1 id="hw__vitals_8h_1autotoc_md7_1s1"><sect2 id="hw__vitals_8h_1autotoc_md7_1s2"><sect3 id="hw__vitals_8h_1autotoc_md7">
<title>Replacement contract</title><para>Provide a translation unit that defines both functions below:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><ref refid="hw__vitals_8h_1ae58df14f30461cb37e8607aca5522846" kindref="member">hw_init()</ref> — called once when the dashboard opens.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="hw__vitals_8h_1ac277bf28fcc192d8dd7cd5b3466a4fa9" kindref="member">hw_get_next_reading()</ref> — called periodically (every ~2 s) by WM_TIMER.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect3></sect2></sect1>
